caption:
We are ending this trip to Havana photographing  some wonderful ballerinas in a classic location. Many thanks to @adarys_ballet and @paloma_classique for being such great models. 
.
.
.
#cuba #havana #irablock #ballet #ballerina #sonyalpha #travelphotography

At the Ajusco restaurant in Cojimar, Cuba they pride themselves on their Mojitos. I was a little surprised when I saw a group of little girls at the bar learning how to make their ‘famous’ drink. I shot some images first and asked questions later. The girls were making alcohol free drinks, of course. The young lady with the pacifier in her mouth eventually removed it to try her alcohol free drink 
I am sure that Ernest Hemingway, who lived near by and was inspired to write the Old Man and the Sea based on the local fishermen would have approved of the girls early training. 
.
.
.
#cuba #cojimar #mojito #irablock #ernesthemingway #travelphotography  #bartender

Im usually napping on the early flight from Miami to Havana. This morning I looked out the window and  saw that our flight path was following the length of the Florida Keys. The colors and shapes were amazing, scenes from another world. My napping stopped - time to grab a few photos. 
.
.
.
#ocean #floridakeys #irablock #flying #patterns #airplaneviews✈️

As I travel to throughout different regions of the world, I am always amazed at how ‘kids’ play. In Cuba where there aren’t hi tech games or smart phones children always find something to do.  Sitting at a cafe in Baracoa I watched as this group found so much joy in running along a wall and jumping over the gaps. 
.
.
.
#cuba #baracoa #irablock #play #kids #joy #childrenatplay #joy #travelphotography

While I was in Santiago, Cuba I visited the Santa Ifigenia Cemetery where José Marti and Fidel Castro are buried.  The changing of the guard ceremony was quite impressive 
#cuba #santiagodecuba #josemarti #fidelcastro #irablock #changingoftheguard #travelphotography

Can you guess what this person has going for him that the average person doesn’t when it comes to coconut tree climbing? Look closely at these images - his nickname is twenty four. Veinticuatro
.
.
.
#cuba #baracoa #coconuts #irablock #travelphotography #treeclimbing #extradigits

Feeling the rhythm of these incredible Caribbean dancers from the “Espiral” group in Santiago, Cuba, brightens my Monday. 

#irablock #travel #santiago #caribbeanmusic

I always find exciting photo opportunities on my morning walks around Santiago, Cuba. This morning we were near the rum factory where I saw a wonderful green Chevy truck. The driver was most cooperative in being photographed, a common trait amongst the Cuban people. I will be sad to leave tomorrow, however I am back in a few weeks. 
.
.
.
#cuba #santiagocuba #trucks #oldtrucks #irablock #travelphotography #chevy #green #sonyalpha

Near the Rio Yumuri I met a family that is trying to preserve this colorful snail that is almost extinct. Can anyone help me with identifying the type of snail?
The first photo is a great grandmother and her great granddaughter. I learned a new word today Bisa Abuela. 
.
.
.
#cuba #baracoa #snails #family #travelphotography #irablock

Tobacco farming is still a major part of the Cuban economy and culture. The process is tedious and laborious, the results are great cigars. Viñales is known for its fantastic tobacco crop. The sorting process is meticulous and is done by Cubans with years of experience 
.
.
#cuba #tobacco #tobaccofarming #irablock #viñales #travelphotography #cigars #cubancigars

Capturing moments in low light adds incredible mood to a photo and helps tell a story. Walking through Viñales, Cuba last week I saw this couple dancing in an empty  restaurant. I was carrying my Sony a7cii with a 35mm F 1.8 lens - my go to setup for low light - the files look really good at high ISO.  The shutter speed  of 1/100 second helped me stop the action. The lens was wide open at f/ 1.8 and my ISO was set at 5000. The moment was caught!
.
.
.
#cuba #viñales #dance #sonyartisan #irablock #sonyalpha #lowlightphotography @sonyalpha

The ballet school in Havana is filled with aspiring ballerinas under incredible pressure to make it to the National Ballet of Cuba.  Only a few make the cut and it becomes a life changing experience. Of course they try to have fun and enjoy the moment 
.
.
.
#cuba #havana #ballet #balletschool #irablock #dance #travelphotography #sonyalpha
